Modifications made by this fork (2026) relative to VulkanMod Reforged:

  Platform / macOS:
  - Fixed the macOS / Apple Silicon startup crash on NeoForge. VulkanMod Reforged crashed with
    "NoClassDefFoundError: org.lwjgl.vulkan.VK" at org.lwjgl.glfw.GLFWVulkan because the bundled
    lwjgl-vulkan is loaded into the game module layer while GLFWVulkan lives in the boot layer, which
    cannot read it. This fork obtains the required Vulkan instance extensions and creates the window
    surface without referencing GLFWVulkan (new class net.vulkanmod.vulkan.VkSurfaceUtil).
  - Added a macOS surface path: CAMetalLayer + VK_EXT_metal_surface (MoltenVK), including the Retina
    contentsScale. Added Windows/Linux (Win32/Xlib/Wayland) surface paths for completeness.
  - Bundled the LWJGL Vulkan/shaderc/vma natives for all desktop platforms (Windows, Linux, macOS
    x86-64 and Apple Silicon) into a single jar.
  - Fixed a case-sensitive shader resource load (terrain_Z.fsh -> terrain_z.fsh).

  Rendering features:
  - Native Vulkan post-process shader pipeline (color grading, volumetric height fog, screen-space
    god-rays) rendered directly in the Vulkan renderer.
  - Sun and moon shadow mapping: a second camera-relative terrain pass into a depth texture, sampled
    by the post-process pass with Vogel-disk PCF and slope-scaled bias; a resolution quality slider.
  - Temporal accumulation (TAA) to smooth shadow shimmer.
  - Render-scale upscaling (render below native resolution, upscale to the swapchain).
  - GPU frame timing (Vulkan timestamp queries) and additional culling paths.

Prior fork modification (VulkanMod Reforged, by Rindw, 2026-06-19): Minecraft 1.21.1 NeoForge
compatibility, release metadata cleanup, and local compatibility fixes.

